## Build and Test

```powershell
.\Build\build.ps1 -ResolveDependency   # install build dependencies (first run)
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Test        # run all Pester tests
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Analyze     # run PSScriptAnalyzer
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Help        # regenerate help files
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList BuildNuget  # build .nupkg artifact
```

## Repository Structure

```
Public/        Exported functions — one file per function, filename = function name
Private/       Internal helpers — never exported
Tests/
  Unit/        Pester 5 unit tests (*Tests.ps1)
  Common/      Shared tests: manifest, help coverage, PSSA
Build/         build.ps1 entry, build.psake.ps1 tasks, build.depend.psd1
Documentation/ PlatyPS markdown help
en-US/         Compiled MAML help
```

## Coding Rules

1. PowerShell 5.1+ compatible unless noted otherwise
2. One exported function per file; file name must match function name
3. Every exported function needs `[CmdletBinding()]` and comment-based help
4. Use `Join-Path` / `$PSScriptRoot` for all paths — no hardcoded paths, no string concatenation
5. Use `-ErrorAction` explicitly; avoid silently swallowing errors
6. Follow approved PS verbs: https://learn.microsoft.com/powershell/scripting/developer/cmdlet/approved-verbs-for-windows-powershell-commands
7. New public functions get a matching test file in `Tests\Unit\<FunctionName>.Tests.ps1`

## Pester 5 Test Syntax

```powershell
Describe 'Get-Something' {
    It 'returns expected value' {
        Get-Something -Input 'x' | Should -Be 'expected'
    }
    It 'calls dependency once' {
        Mock Invoke-Something {}
        Get-Something -Input 'x'
        Should -Invoke Invoke-Something -Times 1 -Exactly
    }
}
```

